"{\"uid\": \"rte.ie-sport-paris-2024-2024-0726-1462073-olympics-podcast-mcclenaghan-takes-the-horse-to-france\", \"text\": \"  Among the Irish in action on Day 1 of the Games is gymnast Rhys McClenaghan, a genuine medal hope in the pommel horse.  Mikey Stafford is joined by Olympic judge Mairead Kavanagh to discuss one of the most competitive disciplines in this year's artisitc gymnastics schedule.  Mairead explains the relative strengths of McClenaghan's opponents and what the judges will be looking out for during Saturday's qualifying at the Bercy Arena.  She also talks to us about the force of nature that is Simone Biles - back to her best after her 'Twisties' ordeal in Tokyo.  Listen to the RT\\u00c9 Olympics Podcast on theRT\\u00c9 Radio Player,Apple Podcasts,Spotify, orwherever you get your podcasts  We need your consent to load this rte-player contentWe use rte-player to manage extra content that can set cookies on your device and collect data about your activity. Please review their details and accept them to load the content.Manage Preferences    \\u00a9 RT\\u00c9 2026. RT\\u00c9.ie is the website of Raidi\\u00f3 Teilif\\u00eds \\u00c9ireann, Ireland's National Public Service Media. RT\\u00c9 is not responsible for the content of external internet sites.  Images Courtesy of Getty Images.\"}"